name: Jefferson
absentee_method: Released as a precinct as first report of the night
nyt_race_description_race: Representative Ann Wagner, a longtime Republican incumbent, finds herself in a tougher-then-usual race to defend her seat against Jill Schupp, a Democtratic state senator. The district is made up of the St. Louis suburbs, and there are signs both in Missouri and nationwide that some suburban voters have tired of President Trump and soured on the Republican Party.
poll_display_race: Polls close at 8 p.m. Eastern time.
